        <briefdescription>
<para>Simulates a single instance with one dispatching rule and returns a gap analysis. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Constructs a fresh DESSimulator, loads <computeroutput>instance</computeroutput>, sets <computeroutput>rule</computeroutput> as the active dispatching rule, runs to completion, and packages the result into a <ref refid="struct_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_validation_1_1_validation_runner_1_1_validation_result" kindref="compound">ValidationResult</ref>. The gap percentage is computed relative to TaillardMetadata.optimum and will be infinite or undefined if optimum is <computeroutput>0</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>instance</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The benchmark instance to simulate. Must have valid TaillardInstance.metadata with a non-zero TaillardMetadata.optimum for gap analysis to be meaningful. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>rule</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The DispatchingRule to apply during the simulation run.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A <ref refid="struct_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_validation_1_1_validation_runner_1_1_validation_result" kindref="compound">ValidationResult</ref> containing the makespan, gap, and bound values for this rule and instance combination. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
