        <name>ValidateConstraints</name>
        <qualifiedname>Assets.Scripts.Scheduling.Validation.ValidationRunner.ValidateConstraints</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_data_1_1_taillard_instance" kindref="compound">TaillardInstance</ref></type>
          <declname>instance</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="namespace_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1af841dd07c9c38276e117696a4dd6fe87" kindref="member">DispatchingRule</ref></type>
          <declname>rule</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Verifies correctness invariants of the DESSimulator against a benchmark instance. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Runs a fresh simulation with <computeroutput>rule</computeroutput> and performs four sequential checks. All violations found across all checks are collected and returned — execution does not stop at the first error. A correct implementation should always return an empty list.</para>
<para>The four checks are:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>Valid times</bold>: every Operation has non-negative Operation.StartTime and Operation.EndTime. A value of <computeroutput>-1</computeroutput> indicates the operation was never scheduled.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Precedence</bold>: for each job, operation <computeroutput>i</computeroutput> must start no earlier than operation <computeroutput>i-1</computeroutput> ends. Violations indicate a sequencing bug in DESSimulator.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>No machine overlap</bold>: no two operations assigned to the same machine may overlap in time. Operations are sorted by start time and checked pairwise. Violations indicate a machine contention bug.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Makespan lower bound</bold>: the achieved makespan must be at or above TaillardMetadata.lower_bound. A violation indicates a bug that produces a schedule that is theoretically impossible.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>A floating-point epsilon of <computeroutput>1e-9</computeroutput> is applied to all time comparisons to guard against rounding errors in double arithmetic.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>instance</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The benchmark instance to validate against. Must have valid TaillardMetadata with a meaningful TaillardMetadata.lower_bound. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>rule</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The DispatchingRule to use for the validation simulation run.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A list of human-readable error strings describing each violation found. Returns an empty list if all constraints are satisfied. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
